<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="182" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,656,899]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,837,863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from Jharbari Forest range, from where the species was collected. The name is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
