<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="182" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1582,2041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1582,1609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Guo, Zhang &amp; Zhu, 2011" authorityName="Guo, Zhang &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2011" box="[673,1175,1583,1609]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Vailimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitibia">
<emphasis box="[673,883,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Vailimia longitibia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Guo, J. Y. &amp; Zhang, F. &amp; Zhu, M. S." box="[890,1175,1583,1609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref2904" refString="Guo, J. Y., Zhang, F. &amp; Zhu, M. S. (2011) One new recorded genus and one new species of the family Salticidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from China. Acta Arachnologica Sinica, 20 (1), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="2011">
Guo, Zhang &amp; Zhu, 
<quantity box="[1120,1175,1583,1609]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.10794" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" unit="in" value="2011.0">2011</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the habitus and palp (
<figureCitation box="[159,289,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1984,2009]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[177,1410,633,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 14–16 male (14 dorsal view; 15 lateral view; 16 frontal view). 17–19 female (17 dorsal view; 18 lateral view; 19 frontal view). Scale bars: 2 mm (14–15, 17–18); 1 mm (16, 19)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887986/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Figs 14–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[301,375,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,191,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 20–22 right male palp (20 ventral view; 21 retrolateral view; 22 dorsal view); 23 chelicerae, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (20–22); 0.5 mm (23)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887988/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">20–22</figureCitation>
), but differs in having a relatively shorter palpal tibia and broader apical cymbial region; RTA with a broad base without a ridge, narrow, directed distally (with a ridge at the base; curved and directed dorsally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guo, Zhang &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,288,1691,1717]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Vailimia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitibia">
<emphasis box="[151,288,1691,1717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">V. longitibia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[349,475,1691,1717]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,191,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 20–22 right male palp (20 ventral view; 21 retrolateral view; 22 dorsal view); 23 chelicerae, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (20–22); 0.5 mm (23)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887988/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Figs 20–22</figureCitation>
herein with 
<bibRefCitation author="Guo, J. Y. &amp; Zhang, F. &amp; Zhu, M. S." box="[615,896,1691,1717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" pagination="1 - 3" refId="ref2904" refString="Guo, J. Y., Zhang, F. &amp; Zhu, M. S. (2011) One new recorded genus and one new species of the family Salticidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from China. Acta Arachnologica Sinica, 20 (1), 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="2011">Guo, Zhang &amp; Zhu 2011</bibRefCitation>
: figs 4–5).
</paragraph>
