<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="185" pageId="4" pageNumber="182" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1582,2041]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,152,611]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,415,1726,1753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[431,536,1727,1754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length: 6.63; carapace: 3.12 long, 2.77 wide; abdomen: 3.51 long, 2.23 wide. Carapace brown, covered with greyish and whitish hairs; eyes surrounded by blackish region; broad white band present on lateral margin; two pairs of tubercles present along the margin of the ocular area, one between the ALEs and PMEs another near the PLEs (
<figureCitation box="[677,764,1835,1861]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1984,2009]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[177,1410,633,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 14–16 male (14 dorsal view; 15 lateral view; 16 frontal view). 17–19 female (17 dorsal view; 18 lateral view; 19 frontal view). Scale bars: 2 mm (14–15, 17–18); 1 mm (16, 19)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887986/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Anterior eyes surrounded by white setae, clypeal region light brown covered with long hairs; ‘cheek region’ covered with four thin transverse white stripes (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1371,1871,1898]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1984,2009]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[177,1410,633,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 14–16 male (14 dorsal view; 15 lateral view; 16 frontal view). 17–19 female (17 dorsal view; 18 lateral view; 19 frontal view). Scale bars: 2 mm (14–15, 17–18); 1 mm (16, 19)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887986/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Eye measurements: AME 0.73, ALE 0.37, PME 0.14, PLE 0.34, AER 2.28, PER 2.54, EFL 1.42. Clypeus height 0.10. Chelicerae light brown with two promarginal teeth and a bifid retromarginal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1186,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,191,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 20–22 right male palp (20 ventral view; 21 retrolateral view; 22 dorsal view); 23 chelicerae, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (20–22); 0.5 mm (23)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887988/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="182">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Sternum pale brown and oval; labium and maxillae pale brown. Legs yellowish brown; leg I &amp; II covered with dense black hairs on ventral region of patellae, tibiae and metatarsi. Leg measurements: I 7.18 (2.11, 1.51, 1.81, 1.03, 0.72); II 5.04 (1.84, 0.76, 1.22, 0.83, 0.39); III 5.97 (2.58, 0.82, 0.80, 1.29, 0.48); IV 5.99 (2.11, 0.93, 1.21, 1.34, 0.40). Abdomen oval, brownish, covered sparsely with blackish setae, having chevron markings mid-dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1213,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1984,2009]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[177,1410,633,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 14–16 male (14 dorsal view; 15 lateral view; 16 frontal view). 17–19 female (17 dorsal view; 18 lateral view; 19 frontal view). Scale bars: 2 mm (14–15, 17–18); 1 mm (16, 19)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887986/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); venter brown with yellow longitudinal lateral margins. Spinnerets brownish. Palps light yellow; palpal tibia with blackish long hairs; cymbium with a patch of dorsal scopulae and white hairs present at the base; RTA long and narrow, with a broad base; embolus long and slender (
<figureCitation box="[518,649,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,191,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 20–22 right male palp (20 ventral view; 21 retrolateral view; 22 dorsal view); 23 chelicerae, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (20–22); 0.5 mm (23)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887988" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887988/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Figs 20–23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,333,359]" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Female</emphasis>
(NZC-ZSI 6593/18). Total length: 9.12; carapace: 4.02 long, 3.16 wide; abdomen: 5.10 long, 3.40 wide. Eye measurements: AME 0.71, ALE, 0.38, PME 0.13, PLE 0.36, AER 2.48, PER 2.93, EFL 1.50. Clypeus height 0.21. Leg measurements: I 6.85 (1.98, 1.47, 1.71, 0.86, 0.83); II 6.19 (2.18, 1.17, 1.18, 0.93, 0.73); III 7.71 (2.99, 1.53, 1.41, 1.12, 0.66), IV 6.82 (2.30, 1.16, 1.46, 1.23, 0.67). Coloration pattern as in male, but differs by following: abdomen with black patches on lateral sides and a short dark brown mid-dorsal stripe above the chevron pattern (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1984,2009]" captionTargetBox="[187,1403,633,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[177,1410,633,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 14–19. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. 14–16 male (14 dorsal view; 15 lateral view; 16 frontal view). 17–19 female (17 dorsal view; 18 lateral view; 19 frontal view). Scale bars: 2 mm (14–15, 17–18); 1 mm (16, 19)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887986/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Epigyne with a pair of oval translucent windows, separated by a narrow septum; copulatory openings present at the anterior region; copulatory ducts broad, arching anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[970,1100,549,576]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1289,1314]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,181,1258]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1264]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. epigyne. 24 cleared, ventral view; 25 vulva, dorsal view; 26 ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887990/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Figs 24, 26</figureCitation>
); spermathecae globular (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1289,1314]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,181,1258]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,181,1264]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. Vailimia jharbari sp. nov. epigyne. 24 cleared, ventral view; 25 vulva, dorsal view; 26 ventral view; 27 vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887990" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887990/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="183">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
